beer.beer_description:
Bearded Seal is our double dry-hopped Hazy IPA we brewed in collaboration with LERVIG in Norway. 

The Bearded Seal, found in Norway, is a heavy set creature with large whiskers. This collaboration needed a big beer. 

Mike from Lervig came to Footscray and caused plenty of havoc in the brewery. Double dry-hopped with a punch-bowl of fruit-forward American hops, we then added pineapple, passionfruit and mango to the ferment. 

Full haze, full juice.

items.badge_description: There's beer in them thar hills! You're setting off on your journey through the world of beer, but be sure to take a little time to get to know each brewery as you go. That's a beer from 10 different breweries. Try 5 more for Level 3!

You may not be able to see through the haze, but that juicy, hoppy goodness goes down smooth. What started as a trend is here to stay. That's 5 different beers with the style of IPA - New England (Imperial or Single), Pale Ale - New England or IPA - Milkshake. Try 5 more for Level 2!
Do you come from the land down under, where beer does flow, and men chunder? That's at least 15 different beers from Australia. Try 5 more for Level 4.
